DependencyInjection
	It is desing pattern in which an object dependency are provided by IOC
	container, instead of creating object it self.
	Depedency Injection, inject one class object into other class object
	and it also inject object value etc........

	Types of DI
		1. Contructor Injection
		2. Setter Method Injection
		3. Feild or Variable Injection
		
	1. Contructor Injection 
			-> Mechanism where the required dependecies of a class are provided to
			it constructor, when the object is Created.
			wiht the help of construcor injection, we can store the value inside objet
			and store one object into another object through parameterized contructor, 
			by using xml or annotaion configration.
			
			e.g 
				class Trainer{
					Student st;
					public Trainer(Student st){
						this.st = st;	
					}
				}
			
	2. Setter Method Injection
			-> mechanism in which spring injects depedencies( one object into another 
			oject, and value inside object ), by calling setter method, 
			after creating the Bean by IOC.
			
			-> it is use for optional dependencies, but it doent guarantee, that 
			required depedencies are available at object creation time, therefore, 
			contructor injection is generally prefered for mandatory depedencies.
			
			-> it supports xml and annotaion based configuration.
			
			
